-- South African Police Round Up 17 Alleged Argentine Hooligans at World Cup
-- Tariq Panja
-- 2010-06-16T09:54:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/south-african-police-round-up-17-alleged-argentine-hooligans-at-world-cup.html

          
          
             South African police say they
rounded up 17 known Argentine soccer hooligans in the country
for the World Cup.  
 The group was tracked to a hotel in Pretoria and will be
sent back home, South African Police Service spokeswoman  Sally De Beer  said in a telephone interview today.  
 Five days before the start of the tournament at least seven
Argentines were detained at Johannesburgâ€™s OR Tambo
International Airport after appearing on a list of known
troublemakers.  
